{
  "text": "Time orchestration or time balance refers to how much time a person invests in work, family, leisure, personal development and sleep. When examining the use of time, one should consider the balance between one's various occupations; does the person find satisfaction in how their life is orchestrated? Finding balance is critical in light of studies that indicate a relationship between the temporal aspects of daily function and human psychology and physiology (e.g., [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ).",
